{"TopicId":203371,"ForumId":112,"TopicTitle":"KSP2 Suggestion: some modifier key \u002B F1 saves to both ScreenShots folder and the UserLoadingScreens folder","CreatedByName":"darthgently","CreatedById":204885,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-06-27T08:08:43Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"darthgently","CreatedById":204885,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-06-27T08:08:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nsee subject\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-06-27T09:04:28Z\u0022 title=\u002206/27/2021 09:04  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EJune 27, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by darthgently\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"jimmymcgoochie","CreatedById":199902,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-06-27T09:01:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUnclear what you mean- do you want this feature to be added to KSP2? Or is this happening to you in KSP 1.12?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"darthgently","CreatedById":204885,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-06-27T09:03:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223996017\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022203371\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221624784503\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022199902\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022jimmymcgoochie\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, jimmymcgoochie said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUnclear what you mean- do you want this feature to be added to KSP2? Or is this happening to you in KSP 1.12?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSorry, I\u0027ll clarify the description.\u00A0 Thanks for pointing that out\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\nIt seems unnecessary to have to rummage through the screenshot folder at some other time when at the time of saving the screen one\u0027s goal is to add it to the loading screens.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"StarSlay3r","CreatedById":209403,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-06-29T22:34:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHello! We recently created a new KSP 2 Suggestions \u0026amp; Development Discussion section, so we\u0027ll be moving all related posts (including this one) over there.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dr. Kerbal","CreatedById":207217,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-07-01T04:01:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223997493\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022203371\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221625006062\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022209403\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022KSPStar\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 6/29/2021 at 3:34 PM, KSPStar said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHello! We recently created a new KSP 2 Suggestions \u0026amp; Development Discussion section, so we\u0027ll be moving all related posts (including this one) over there.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI know. And thanks \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/123837-dman979/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022123837\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/123837-dman979/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Dman979\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0and the entire moderator team for adding this thread, Means a lot to me.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223996006\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022203371\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221624781323\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022204885\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022darthgently\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 6/27/2021 at 1:08 AM, darthgently said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nsee subject\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYa. This is actually a great idea as the F-xx keys aren\u0027t use for anything (as we know yet). and when pressing\u00A0 f-12 on KPS Steam things go a bit messy.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"darthgently","CreatedById":204885,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-07-01T13:01:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223998202\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022203371\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221625112095\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022207217\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Dr. Kerbal\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, Dr. Kerbal said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI know. And thanks \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/123837-dman979/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022123837\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/123837-dman979/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Dman979\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0and the entire moderator team for adding this thread, Means a lot to me.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYa. This is actually a great idea as the F-xx keys aren\u0027t use for anything (as we know yet). and when pressing\u00A0 f-12 on KPS Steam things go a bit messy.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot sure if you are kidding as the Fn keys get a lot of use, and F1 takes a screen shot and puts it in the ScreenShots directory off the main KSP director.\u00A0 The idea is that something like Alt-F1 would put the screenshot in UserLoadingScreens as well as ScreenShots.\u00A0 F12 just turns the aero drag visual indicators on/off last I checked, but I don\u0027t run via Steam so maybe Steam layers something on top of that\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bej Kerman","CreatedById":182413,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-07-01T13:27:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou want an option for your screenshot to show up on the loading screen?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"pandaman","CreatedById":130621,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-07-02T18:59:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot in itself a bad idea, but surely it\u0027s not that hard to copy the screenshots you want in to the loading screen folder.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"darthgently","CreatedById":204885,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-07-03T01:17:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223999037\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022203371\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221625252351\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022130621\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022pandaman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, pandaman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot in itself a bad idea, but surely it\u0027s not that hard to copy the screenshots you want in to the loading screen folder.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, because that is what computers are for.\u00A0 Automating and simplifying\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}